main event: A round pink object, the size of a basketball held at arm's length, was observed in the sky in June 1956.
interesting points: The object was estimated to be at an altitude of one to two thousand feet., The sighting lasted from 8:11 to 8:16 PM., The witness, Howard Teschner, reported the sighting to the AFISO at 0330 hrs., The object was still in sight at the time of the report., No additional details were provided in the report.
